{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868739399,"sessionID":"ses_285fa8df0ffeLn6Q7UsZ3LEyZT","part":{"id":"prt_d7a067b64001wQJ1pzjR8Jk2ol","messageID":"msg_d7a067162001Lrby5IcvK5qpIN","sessionID":"ses_285fa8df0ffeLn6Q7UsZ3LEyZT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: Redis Storage Implementation\n2: \n3: ## AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `pkg/store` |\n8: | **Language** | Go |\n9: | **Size** | M (Medium) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the Redis storage provider for the Session Store interface defined in AR-012. This proposal delivers a production-ready Redis backend that:\n17: \n18: 1. **Implements the Store Interface**: Full implementation of all 8 Store methods using go-redis/v9\n19: 2. **Provides Atomic Operations**: Pipeline-based multi-command transactions for data consistency\n20: 3. **Maintains Secondary Indexes**: ZSET-based expiry and activity tracking for efficient garbage collection\n21: 4. **Supports Configuration via Environment**: Flexible connection and authentication setup\n22: \n23: This implementation enables AgentCube to use Redis as the session metadata backend, supporting high-frequency read/write operations and time-based queries for session lifecycle management.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Scope\n28: \n29: ### In Scope\n30: \n31: | Item | Detail |\n32: |------|--------|\n33: | **Redis Implementation** | `store_redis.go` — Complete Store interface implementation |\n34: | **Connection Management** | Environment-based Redis client configuration |\n35: | **Atomic Operations** | Pipeline-based SETNX + ZADD, DEL + ZREM |\n36: | **Error Handling** | Redis-specific error translation to `ErrNotFound` |\n37: | **Index Management** | ZSET operations for expiry and last-activity tracking |\n38: | **Helper Functions** | Key generation, JSON serialization, batch loading |\n39: \n40: ### Out of Scope\n41: \n42: - Valkey implementation (covered in separate AR or future extension)\n43: - SQL database implementations (can be added via same interface)\n44: - Redis Cluster-specific hash tag handling\n45: - Redis Sentinel or Redis Cluster automatic failover configuration\n46: - Connection pooling tuning beyond library defaults\n47: - TLS/SSL configuration (handled via Redis URL or library defaults)\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Design\n52: \n53: ### File Structure\n54: \n55: | File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n56: |------|------|--------------|\n57: | `pkg/store/store.go` | Store interface and ErrNotFound definition | ~50 |\n58: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Redis implementation with go-redis/v9 | ~250 |\n59: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Singleton accessor and provider selection | ~80 |\n60: \n61: ### Redis Implementation (`redisStore`)\n62: \n63: ```go\n64: type redisStore struct {\n65:     cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n66:     sessionPrefix        string           // \"session:\"\n67:     expiryIndexKey       string           // \"session:expiry\"\n68:     lastActivityIndexKey string           // \"session:last_activity\"\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### Key Patterns\n73: \n74: | Pattern | Value | Description |\n75: |---------|-------|-------------|\n76: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session data keys |\n77: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET for expiry tracking |\n78: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET for activity tracking |\n79: | Session Key | `session:{sessionID}` | Primary key format |\n80: \n81: ### Environment Configuration\n82: \n83: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n84: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n85: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection (case-insensitive) |\n86: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n87: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive) |\n88: \n89: ### Connection Options\n90: \n91: ```go\n92: &redisv9.Options{\n93:     Addr:     redisAddr,     // From REDIS_ADDR\n94:     Password: redisPassword, // From REDIS_PASSWORD (if required)\n95: }\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## Operations Specification\n101: \n102: ### Ping — Connectivity Verification\n103: \n104: ```\n105: Ping(ctx)\n106:     │\n107:     ▼\n108: PING command\n109:     │\n110:     ▼\n111: Expect \"PONG\" response\n112:     │\n113:     ▼\n114: Return nil if PONG, error otherwise\n115: ```\n116: \n117: **Redis Command**: `PING`\n118: \n119: ### GetSandboxBySessionID — Retrieve by ID\n120: \n121: ```\n122: GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n123:     │\n124:     ▼\n125: GET session:{sessionID}\n126:     │\n127:     ▼\n128: If redis.Nil:\n129:     └── Return ErrNotFound\n130: If other error:\n131:     └── Return wrapped error\n132: If success:\n133:     └── Unmarshal JSON → *SandboxInfo\n134: ```\n135: \n136: **Redis Command**: `GET {key}`\n137: **Error Translation**: `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound`\n138: \n139: ### StoreSandbox — Atomic Create with Indexing\n140: \n141: ```\n142: StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n143:     │\n144:     ▼\n145: Validate: sandbox != nil\n146:     │\n147:     ▼\n148: Validate: !sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero()\n149:     │\n150:     ▼\n151: Serialize to JSON\n152:     │\n153:     ▼\n154: Pipeline:\n155: ├─ SETNX session:{id} <json>\n156: ├─ ZADD session:expiry <expiresAt.Unix()> {id}\n157: └─ ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix()> {id}\n158:     │\n159:     ▼\n160: Execute pipeline\n161:     │\n162:     ▼\n163: If any error: return error\n164: ```\n165: \n166: **Redis Commands**: `SETNX`, `ZADD` (expiry), `ZADD` (activity)\n167: **Atomicity**: All commands executed in single pipeline\n168: \n169: ### UpdateSandbox — Update Existing Record\n170: \n171: ```\n172: UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n173:     │\n174:     ▼\n175: Validate: sandbox != nil\n176:     │\n177:     ▼\n178: Serialize to JSON\n179:     │\n180:     ▼\n181: SET session:{id} <json> XX\n182:     │\n183:     ▼\n184: If SET returns false (key not exists):\n185:     └── Return error: \"key not exists\"\n186: If success:\n187:     └── Return nil\n188:     \n189: Note: Does NOT modify ZSET indices\n190: ```\n191: \n192: **Redis Command**: `SET {key} {value} XX`\n193: **Behavior**: XX flag requires key to exist; returns false if absent\n194: \n195: ### DeleteSandboxBySessionID — Atomic Cleanup\n196: \n197: ```\n198: DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n199:     │\n200:     ▼\n201: Pipeline:\n202: ├─ DEL session:{id}\n203: ├─ ZREM session:expiry {id}\n204: └─ ZREM session:last_activity {id}\n205:     │\n206:     ▼\n207: Execute pipeline\n208:     │\n209:     ▼\n210: Return error if any command fails\n211: ```\n212: \n213: **Redis Commands**: `DEL`, `ZREM` (expiry), `ZREM` (activity)\n214: **Atomicity**: All cleanup operations in single pipeline\n215: \n216: ### ListExpiredSandboxes — Query by Expiry\n217: \n218: ```\n219: ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)\n220:     │\n221:     ▼\n222: If limit <= 0:\n223:     └── Return nil, nil\n224:     │\n225:     ▼\n226: ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}\n227:     │\n228:     ▼\n229: For each sessionID in results:\n230:     ├─ GET session:{id}\n231:     ├─ If exists: unmarshal and add to results\n232:     └─ If nil (orphan): skip\n233:     │\n234:     ▼\n235: Return []*SandboxInfo\n236: ```\n237: \n238: **Redis Commands**: `ZRANGEBYSCORE` followed by pipelined `GET`\n239: **Tolerance**: Missing keys (orphan ZSET members) are skipped\n240: \n241: ### ListInactiveSandboxes — Query by Activity\n242: \n243: ```\n244: ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)\n245:     │\n246:     ▼\n247: If limit <= 0:\n248:     └── Return nil, nil\n249:     │\n250:     ▼\n251: ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}\n252:     │\n253:     ▼\n254: For each sessionID in results:\n255:     ├─ GET session:{id}\n256:     ├─ If exists: unmarshal and add to results\n257:     └─ If nil (orphan): skip\n258:     │\n259:     ▼\n260: Return []*SandboxInfo\n261: ```\n262: \n263: **Redis Commands**: `ZRANGEBYSCORE` (on activity index) + pipelined `GET`\n264: **Note**: Same pattern as ListExpiredSandboxes, different ZSET key\n265: \n266: ### UpdateSessionLastActivity — Bump Activity Timestamp\n267: \n268: ```\n269: UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)\n270:     │\n271:     ▼\n272: Validate: sessionID != \"\"\n273:     │\n274:     ▼\n275: If at.IsZero():\n276:     └── at = time.Now()\n277:     │\n278:     ▼\n279: GET session:{sessionID} (check existence)\n280:     │\n281:     ▼\n282: If key not exists:\n283:     └── Return ErrNotFound\n284:     │\n285:     ▼\n286: ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}\n287:     │\n288:     ▼\n289: Return error if ZADD fails\n290: ```\n291: \n292: **Redis Commands**: `GET` (existence check), `ZADD`\n293: **Semantics**: Returns ErrNotFound if session doesn't exist\n294: \n295: ### Close — Graceful Shutdown\n296: \n297: ```\n298: Close()\n299:     │\n300:     ▼\n301: cli.Close()\n302:     │\n303:     ▼\n304: Return nil\n305: ```\n306: \n307: **Redis Command**: `Close()` on go-redis client\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ## Helper Functions\n312: \n313: ### Key Generation\n314: \n315: ```go\n316: func (rs *redisStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n317:     return rs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n318: }\n319: ```\n320: \n321: ### Batch Loading\n322: \n323: ```go\n324: func (rs *redisStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, ids []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n325: ```\n326: \n327: - Builds keys from session IDs\n328: - Uses pipelined GET for efficiency\n329: - Skips nil results (orphan handling)\n330: - Unmarshals JSON for valid results\n331: \n332: ---\n333: \n334: ## Error Handling\n335: \n336: | Scenario | Redis Response | Return Value |\n337: |----------|---------------|--------------|\n338: | Key not found | `redis.Nil` | `ErrNotFound` |\n339: | Connection error | Connection error | Wrapped error |\n340: | Pipeline error | Command error | Command error |\n341: | SETXX miss | `false` / not \"OK\" | `errors.New(\"key not exists\")` |\n342: | Nil sandbox | N/A (pre-validation) | `errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")` |\n343: | Zero ExpiresAt | N/A (pre-validation) | `errors.New(\"ExpiresAt is zero\")` |\n344: \n345: ---\n346: \n347: ## Impact Analysis\n348: \n349: ### Files Created\n350: \n351: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n352: |------|-------------|-------------|\n353: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | ~250 | Redis implementation |\n354: | `pkg/store/store.go` | ~50 | Interface definition |\n355: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | ~80 | Singleton and provider selection |\n356: \n357: ### Dependencies Added\n358: \n359: ```go\n360: import (\n361:     \"context\"\n362:     \"encoding/json\"\n363:     \"errors\"\n364:     \"os\"\n365:     \"strings\"\n366:     \"sync\"\n367:     \"time\"\n368:     \n369:     redisv9 \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n370:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n371:     \n372:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n373: )\n374: ```\n375: \n376: | Package | Purpose |\n377: |---------|---------|\n378: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client library |\n379: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging for initialization errors |\n380: \n381: ### Downstream Consumers\n382: \n383: | Consumer | Usage |\n384: |----------|-------|\n385: | Session Manager | `Storage()` accessor for session CRUD |\n386: | Idle Cleanup Worker | `ListInactiveSandboxes` for GC |\n387: | Expiry Cleanup Worker | `ListExpiredSandboxes` for GC |\n388: \n389: ### Performance Characteristics\n390: \n391: | Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n392: |-----------|------------|-------|\n393: | Get | O(1) | Single key lookup |\n394: | Store | O(1) per command | Pipeline of 3 commands |\n395: | Update | O(1) | Single SET with XX |\n396: | Delete | O(1) per command | Pipeline of 3 commands |\n397: | List (expired/inactive) | O(log n + m) | ZRANGEBYSCORE + m GETs |\n398: | Activity Update | O(log n) | ZADD on sorted set |\n399: \n400: ---\n401: \n402: ## Alternatives Considered\n403: \n404: ### Alternative 1: Use Redis Transactions (MULTI/EXEC) instead of Pipelines\n405: \n406: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n407: |--------|------------|\n408: | **Pros** | True atomicity with isolation; rollback capability |\n409: | **Cons** | Higher overhead; blocking on server; overkill for independent commands |\n410: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Pipelines provide sufficient atomicity for independent commands (no cross-key dependencies) with lower overhead |\n411: \n412: ### Alternative 2: Use Lua Scripts for Complex Operations\n413: \n414: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n415: |--------|------------|\n416: | **Pros** | Server-side execution; guaranteed atomicity; reduces round trips |\n417: | **Cons** | Harder to debug; Lua expertise required; harder to maintain |\n418: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Current operations are simple enough for pipelined commands; Lua adds unnecessary complexity |\n419: \n420: ### Alternative 3: Use Redis Hash instead of JSON String\n421: \n422: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n423: |--------|------------|\n424: | **Pros** | Field-level access; partial updates possible |\n425: | **Cons** | More complex serialization; nested structures (EntryPoints) don't map well |\n426: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — JSON provides clean mapping to Go structs; full document replacement is acceptable for session metadata |\n427: \n428: ### Alternative 4: Use Separate Keys for Index instead of ZSET\n429: \n430: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n431: |--------|------------|\n432: | **Pros** | Simpler mental model; key scanning for cleanup |\n433: | **Cons** | Inefficient range queries; key scanning is O(n) |\n434: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — ZSET provides O(log n + m) range queries essential for efficient GC |\n435: \n436: ### Alternative 5: Cache Connection Options in Struct\n437: \n438: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n439: |--------|------------|\n440: | **Pros** | Reconnection possible; expose more options |\n441: | **Cons** | More complex struct; go-redis handles reconnection internally |\n442: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Store client only; go-redis v9 has built-in connection pooling and reconnection |\n443: \n444: ---\n445: \n446: ## Risks and Mitigations\n447: \n448: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n449: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n450: | Redis connection failure at startup | Low | High | `initStore` logs fatal via klog; operator must check configuration |\n451: | Orphan ZSET members after partial failures | Low | Low | List loaders skip missing keys; periodic full scan can clean up |\n452: | Memory pressure from large session sets | Medium | Medium | ZSET with Unix timestamps enables efficient expiry-based cleanup |\n453: | Pipeline partial failure | Low | Medium | All pipeline commands checked; errors returned to caller |\n454: | JSON serialization failure | Low | High | Input validation; proper struct tags on types.SandboxInfo |\n455: \n456: ---\n457: \n458: ## Verification\n459: \n460: ### Unit Tests\n461: \n462: ```bash\n463: # Run all store tests\n464: make test PKG=./pkg/store/...\n465: \n466: # Run with race detector\n467: go test -race ./pkg/store/...\n468: \n469: # Run specific Redis tests\n470: go test -v ./pkg/store/... -run \"TestRedis\"\n471: ```\n472: \n473: ### Integration Tests (requires Redis)\n474: \n475: ```bash\n476: # Start Redis\n477: docker run -d -p 6379:6379 redis:latest\n478: \n479: # Run integration tests\n480: go test -v ./pkg/store/... -tags=integration -redis-addr=localhost:6379\n481: ```\n482: \n483: ### Manual Verification\n484: \n485: ```bash\n486: # Build verification\n487: go build ./pkg/store/...\n488: \n489: # Interface compliance check\n490: go build ./...\n491: \n492: # Lint check\n493: make lint PKG=./pkg/store/...\n494: ```\n495: \n496: ### Test Scenarios\n497: \n498: | Scenario | Expected Result |\n499: |----------|-----------------|\n500: | Store and retrieve sandbox | Success, data matches |\n501: | Get non-existent session | ErrNotFound returned |\n502: | Update existing session | Success, data updated |\n503: | Update non-existent session | Error \"key not exists\" |\n504: | Delete session | Not found on subsequent get |\n505: | List expired sessions | Returns only expired entries |\n506: | List with limit=0 | Returns nil, nil |\n507: | Update activity for missing session | ErrNotFound returned |\n508: | Orphan ZSET member | Skipped during list, no error |\n509: | Concurrent stores | All succeed (different session IDs) |\n510: \n511: ---\n512: \n513: ## References\n514: \n515: - [Session Store Design](session-store/design.md) — Detailed design document\n516: - [Session Store Specification](session-store/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n517: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n518: - [go-redis v9 Documentation](https://github.com/redis/go-redis) — Redis client reference\n519: - [Redis Commands](https://redis.io/commands/) — Redis command reference\n520: \n521: ---\n522: \n523: ## Success Criteria\n524: \n525: 1. ✅ All 8 Store interface methods implemented for Redis\n526: 2. ✅ Pipeline-based atomic operations for Store and Delete\n527: 3. ✅ `ErrNotFound` returned for missing keys\n528: 4. ✅ ZSET indexes correctly maintained\n529: 5. ✅ Environment-based configuration works\n530: 6. ✅ All integration tests pass against Redis instance\n531: 7. ✅ Race detector shows no issues\n532: 8. ✅ `Storage()` singleton properly initializes via sync.Once\n533: \n534: ---\n535: \n536: *AR-013 — Module: pkg/store — Language: Go — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 536 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: Redis Storage Implementation\n\n## AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/store` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Redis storage provider for the Session Store interface defined in AR-012. This proposal delivers a production-ready Redis backend that:\n\n1. **Implements the Store Interface**: Full implementation of all 8 Store methods using go-redis/v9\n2. **Provides Atomic Operations**: Pipeline-based multi-command transactions for data consistency\n3. **Maintains Secondary Indexes**: ZSET-based expiry and activity tracking for efficient garbage collection","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775868739376,"end":1775868739395}}}}
