{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868861841,"sessionID":"ses_285fa8df0ffeLn6Q7UsZ3LEyZT","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0696a2001DSA1XnigaPeAq0","messageID":"msg_d7a067f81001ryDbkAazOS5Yb9","sessionID":"ses_285fa8df0ffeLn6Q7UsZ3LEyZT","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: Valkey Storage Implementation\n\n## AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/store` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | S (Small) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a Valkey storage provider as an alternative to the existing Redis backend for the Session Store interface. This proposal delivers a production-ready Valkey implementation that:\n\n1. **Implements the Store Interface**: Full implementation of all 8 Store methods using `valkey-go` client\n2. **Provides Atomic Operations**: `DoMulti`-based multi-command transactions for data consistency\n3. **Maintains Secondary Indexes**: ZSET-based expiry and activity tracking for efficient garbage collection\n4. **Supports Configuration via Environment**: Flexible connection, authentication, and client behavior setup\n\nThis implementation enables AgentCube to use Valkey as an alternative session metadata backend, providing deployment flexibility and vendor neutrality while maintaining full compatibility with the existing Redis-based data model.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Valkey Implementation** | `store_valkey.go` — Complete Store interface implementation |\n| **Connection Management** | Environment-based Valkey client configuration |\n| **Atomic Operations** | `DoMulti` for SETNX + ZADD, DEL + ZREM |\n| **Error Handling** | Valkey-specific error translation to `ErrNotFound` |\n| **Index Management** | ZSET operations for expiry and last-activity tracking |\n| **Helper Functions** | Key generation, JSON serialization, batch loading via MGET |\n| **Singleton Update** | Extend `singleton.go` to support `STORE_TYPE=valkey` |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Changes to `Store` interface definition\n- Modifications to `SandboxInfo` type or serialization format\n- New features beyond existing Redis functionality\n- Migration tooling between Redis and Valkey backends\n- Changes to client-go or other packages\n- Redis Cluster-specific hash tag handling (deployment consideration)\n- TLS/SSL configuration (handled via library defaults)\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File Structure\n\n| File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n|------|------|--------------|\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation with valkey-go | ~200 |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Update singleton to support valkey type | ~+10 |\n\n### Valkey Implementation (`valkeyStore`)\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n    sessionPrefix        string          // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string          // \"session:expiry\"\n    lastActivityIndexKey string          // \"session:last_activity\"\n}\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n| Pattern | Value | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session data keys |\n| `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET for expiry tracking |\n| `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET for activity tracking |\n| Session Key | `session:{sessionID}` | Primary key format |\n\n### Environment Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection; set to `valkey` (case-insensitive) |\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Valkey server addresses (comma-separated for cluster) |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive) |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | - | Set to `true` to enable `DisableCache` option |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | - | Set to `true` to enable `ForceSingleClient` option |\n\n### Connection Options\n\n```go\nvalkey.ClientOption{\n    InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n    Password:    valkeyPassword,\n    DisableCache: disableCache,       // from VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\n    ForceSingleClient: forceSingle,   // from VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Operations Specification\n\n### Ping — Connectivity Verification\n\n```\nPing(ctx)\n    │\n    ▼\nB().Ping() command\n    │\n    ▼\nExpect \"PONG\" string response\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn nil if PONG, error otherwise\n```\n\n**Valkey API**: `B().Ping()`\n**Response**: String \"PONG\"\n\n### GetSandboxBySessionID — Retrieve by ID\n\n```\nGetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n    │\n    ▼\nB().Get().Key(session:{sessionID})\n    │\n    ▼\nIf IsValkeyNil:\n    └── Return ErrNotFound\nIf other error:\n    └── Return wrapped error\nIf success:\n    └── Unmarshal JSON → *SandboxInfo\n```\n\n**Valkey API**: `B().Get().Key(key)`\n**Error Translation**: `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound`\n\n### StoreSandbox — Atomic Create with Indexing\n\n```\nStoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate: sandbox != nil\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate: !sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero()\n    │\n    ▼\nSerialize to JSON\n    │\n    ▼\nDoMulti:\n├─ SETNX session:{id} <json>\n├─ ZADD session:expiry <expiresAt.Unix()> {id}\n└─ ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix()> {id}\n    │\n    ▼\nExecute DoMulti\n    │\n    ▼\nIf any error: return error\n```\n\n**Valkey API**: `SETNX`, `ZADD` via `DoMulti`\n**Atomicity**: All commands executed in single `DoMulti` block\n\n### UpdateSandbox — Update Existing Record\n\n```\nUpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate: sandbox != nil\n    │\n    ▼\nSerialize to JSON\n    │\n    ▼\nB().Set().Key(key).Value(json).XX()\n    │\n    ▼\nIf response ToString() != \"OK\":\n    └── Return error: \"key not exists\"\nIf success:\n    └── Return nil\n    \nNote: Does NOT modify ZSET indices\n```\n\n**Valkey API**: `SET ... XX`\n**Behavior**: XX flag requires key to exist; check OK response\n\n### DeleteSandboxBySessionID — Atomic Cleanup\n\n```\nDeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n    │\n    ▼\nDoMulti:\n├─ DEL session:{id}\n├─ ZREM session:expiry {id}\n└─ ZREM session:last_activity {id}\n    │\n    ▼\nExecute DoMulti\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn error if any command fails\n```\n\n**Valkey API**: `DEL`, `ZREM` via `DoMulti`\n**Atomicity**: All cleanup operations in single `DoMulti` block\n\n### ListExpiredSandboxes — Query by Expiry\n\n```\nListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)\n    │\n    ▼\nIf limit <= 0:\n    └── Return nil, nil\n    │\n    ▼\nZrangebyscore session:expiry Min(\"-inf\") Max(\"{before.Unix()}\") Limit(0, limit)\n    │\n    ▼\nMGET session:{id1} session:{id2} ...\n    │\n    ▼\nFor each result:\n    ├─ If not empty: unmarshal and add to results\n    └─ If empty (orphan): skip\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn []*SandboxInfo\n```\n\n**Valkey API**: `Zrangebyscore` + `Mget`\n**Tolerance**: Missing keys (orphan ZSET members) are skipped\n**Note**: MGET requires keys in same slot for clustered deployments\n\n### ListInactiveSandboxes — Query by Activity\n\n```\nListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)\n    │\n    ▼\nIf limit <= 0:\n    └── Return nil, nil\n    │\n    ▼\nZrangebyscore session:last_activity Min(\"-inf\") Max(\"{before.Unix()}\") Limit(0, limit)\n    │\n    ▼\nMGET session:{id1} session:{id2} ...\n    │\n    ▼\nFor each result:\n    ├─ If not empty: unmarshal and add to results\n    └─ If empty (orphan): skip\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn []*SandboxInfo\n```\n\n**Valkey API**: `Zrangebyscore` (on activity index) + `Mget`\n**Note**: Same pattern as ListExpiredSandboxes, different ZSET key\n\n### UpdateSessionLastActivity — Bump Activity Timestamp\n\n```\nUpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate: sessionID != \"\"\n    │\n    ▼\nIf at.IsZero():\n    └── at = time.Now()\n    │\n    ▼\nB().Exists().Key(session:{sessionID})\n    │\n    ▼\nIf result != 1:\n    └── Return ErrNotFound\n    │\n    ▼\nB().Zadd().Key(session:last_activity).ScoreMember(float64(at.Unix()), sessionID)\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn error if ZADD fails\n```\n\n**Valkey API**: `Exists`, `Zadd`\n**Semantics**: Returns ErrNotFound if session doesn't exist\n\n### Close — Graceful Shutdown\n\n```\nClose()\n    │\n    ▼\nvs.cli.Close()\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn nil\n```\n\n**Valkey API**: `Close()` on valkey client\n\n---\n\n## Helper Functions\n\n### Key Generation\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n    return vs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n}\n```\n\n### Batch Loading\n\n```go\nfunc (vs *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, ids []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n```\n\n- Builds keys from session IDs using `sessionKey`\n- Uses single `Mget` for efficiency\n- Skips empty string results (orphan handling)\n- Unmarshals JSON for valid results\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n| Scenario | Valkey Response | Return Value |\n|----------|-----------------|--------------|\n| Key not found | `IsValkeyNil` | `ErrNotFound` |\n| Connection error | Connection error | Wrapped error |\n| DoMulti error | Command error | Command error |\n| SETXX miss | Response not OK | `errors.New(\"key not exists\")` |\n| Nil sandbox | N/A (pre-validation) | `errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")` |\n| Zero ExpiresAt | N/A (pre-validation) | `errors.New(\"ExpiresAt is zero\")` |\n| Empty sessionID | N/A (pre-validation) | `errors.New(\"session id is empty\")` |\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files Created/Modified\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | ~200 | Valkey implementation |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | ~+10 | Add valkeyStoreType selector |\n\n### Dependencies Added\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"encoding/json\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"strings\"\n    \"sync\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n    \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n    \n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging for initialization errors |\n\n### Provider Selection (singleton.go)\n\nExtend `initStore()` to support `valkeyStoreType`:\n\n```go\nconst (\n    redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n    valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n)\n\nfunc initStore() error {\n    storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n    if storeType == \"\" {\n        storeType = redisStoreType\n    }\n    \n    switch storeType {\n    case redisStoreType:\n        // existing Redis init\n    case valkeyStoreType:\n        // new Valkey init\n    default:\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %s\", storeType)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Session Manager | `Storage()` accessor for session CRUD |\n| Idle Cleanup Worker | `ListInactiveSandboxes` for GC |\n| Expiry Cleanup Worker | `ListExpiredSandboxes` for GC |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n|-----------|------------|-------|\n| Get | O(1) | Single key lookup |\n| Store | O(1) per command | `DoMulti` of 3 commands |\n| Update | O(1) | Single SET with XX |\n| Delete | O(1) per command | `DoMulti` of 3 commands |\n| List (expired/inactive) | O(log n + m) | Zrangebyscore + MGET |\n| Activity Update | O(log n) | Zadd on sorted set |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Redis Client for Valkey (Protocol Compatibility)\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | No additional dependency; Valkey is Redis protocol-compatible |\n| **Cons** | Misses Valkey-specific optimizations; unclear semantics |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Native Valkey client provides better performance, clearer dependencies, and access to Valkey-specific features |\n\n### Alternative 2: Unified Client Abstraction\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Single interface for all backends; reduced code duplication |\n| **Cons** | Adds complexity; clients have different API shapes; harder to maintain |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Separate implementations are clearer; `sync.Once` singleton already provides clean provider selection |\n\n### Alternative 3: Plugin Architecture\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Dynamic backend loading; extensible without recompilation |\n| **Cons** | Over-engineering for 2 backends; Go plugins are complex and less idiomatic |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** (Future consideration) — Can be revisited if 3+ backends become necessary |\n\n### Alternative 4: Continue with Redis Only\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Single backend to maintain; proven implementation |\n| **Cons** | No vendor choice; Valkey adoption growing; licensing preferences vary |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Low implementation cost; provides valuable deployment flexibility |\n\n---\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Valkey client library differences | Low | Medium | Thorough testing; handle `IsValkeyNil` vs Redis `Nil` |\n| MGET slot alignment (clustered Valkey) | Low | Low | Document deployment consideration; use hashtag patterns if needed |\n| Dependency maintenance | Low | Low | Valkey Go client actively maintained by Valkey IO project |\n| Configuration complexity | Low | Low | Clear documentation; validation at startup |\n| Connection failure at startup | Low | High | `initStore` logs fatal via klog; operator must check configuration |\n| Orphan ZSET members after partial failures | Low | Low | List loaders skip missing keys; periodic full scan can clean up |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all store tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/store/...\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./pkg/store/...\n\n# Run specific Valkey tests\ngo test -v ./pkg/store/... -run \"TestValkey\"\n```\n\n### Integration Tests (requires Valkey)\n\n```bash\n# Start Valkey\ndocker run -d -p 6379:6379 valkey/valkey:latest\n\n# Run integration tests\ngo test -v ./pkg/store/... -tags=integration -valkey-addr=localhost:6379\n```\n\n### Manual Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/store/...\n\n# Interface compliance check\ngo build ./...\n\n# Lint check\nmake lint PKG=./pkg/store/...\n```\n\n### Test Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----------|-----------------|\n| Store and retrieve sandbox | Success, data matches |\n| Get non-existent session | ErrNotFound returned |\n| Update existing session | Success, data updated |\n| Update non-existent session | Error \"key not exists\" |\n| Delete session | Not found on subsequent get |\n| List expired sessions | Returns only expired entries |\n| List with limit=0 | Returns nil, nil |\n| Update activity for missing session | ErrNotFound returned |\n| Orphan ZSET member | Skipped during list, no error |\n| Concurrent stores | All succeed (different session IDs) |\n| STORE_TYPE=valkey selection | Valkey implementation initialized |\n| STORE_TYPE unset (default) | Redis implementation initialized |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [Session Store Design](session-store/design.md) — Detailed design document\n- [Session Store Specification](session-store/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n- [AR-013 Proposal](proposal.md) — Redis implementation (this file replaced)\n- [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n- [Valkey Go Client](https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go) — Valkey client reference\n- [Valkey Documentation](https://valkey.io/) — Valkey server reference\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ All 8 Store interface methods implemented for Valkey\n2. ✅ `DoMulti`-based atomic operations for Store and Delete\n3. ✅ `ErrNotFound` returned for missing keys (via `IsValkeyNil`)\n4. ✅ ZSET indexes correctly maintained\n5. ✅ Environment-based configuration works (VALKEY_* variables)\n6. ✅ `STORE_TYPE=valkey` correctly selects Valkey provider\n7. ✅ All integration tests pass against Valkey instance\n8. ✅ Race detector shows no issues\n9. ✅ `Storage()` singleton properly initializes via `sync.Once`\n\n---\n\n*AR-014 — Module: pkg/store — Language: Go — Size: S*\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775868861796,"end":1775868861837}}}}
